  "text": "Wise [CITATION_1] commenced a research paper entitled 'Public management reform: Competing drivers of change' that \"Public management reforms often are portrayed as part of a global wave of change, and all organizational change is interpreted within a single reform paradigm that is rooted in economics and market-based principles. Reforms outside this paradigm go unnoticed\" [12, p. 555 ]. The New Public Management is therefore in keeping with the global changes which are rooted in finances, institutional, political and ideological changes in which organizations must operate.",
